# Project Structure Guide

## Directory Organization
- The main content is stored in the `hd_src/` directory
- Each document type has its own subdirectory (e.g., [hd_src/food_preferences/](mdc:hd_src/food_preferences))

## File Naming Conventions
- Files are named using the pattern: `[category].[filetype].md`
  - Example: [food_preferences.aiguide.md](mdc:hd_src/food_preferences/food_preferences.aiguide.md)
  - Example: [food_preferences.template.md](mdc:hd_src/food_preferences/food_preferences.template.md)

## File Types
- `template.md`: The actual document template that will be filled with user data
- `aiguide.md`: Instructions for AI on how to create, update and work with the template

## Cross-Document References
- Use double bracket links: `[[DocumentName]]` for references
- Special comments for cross-document synchronization
